HEADWORD: Conceptualism
<hw>Con*cep"tu*al*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Metaph.)</fld> <def>A theory, intermediate between realism and
nominalism, that the mind has the power of forming for itself general
conceptions of individual or single objects.</def>
<rj><au>Stewart.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Conceptualist</ent>⟦br⟧
